    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Don't think so. The easier for most websites will be to style a list like they already style lists. They could reuse the styles they have for ul/li and this will just work™. I even think most of them will already have a search page with a list of refinements (handled server-side) which will be rendered using ul/li.\n\n:8ball: here! I will be happy to discover the opposite when we go further and do the needed work to put back `<ul><li>`.\n",
